{"TopicId":150647,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"initRotation and node_stack","CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-23T02:42:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-23T02:42:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes initRotation impact how stacked nodes get attached? \u00A0Is it supposed to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have some modded lander legs that include a node_stack for convenience (strategically lined up with a node_stack on the part they\u0027re intended to mate with).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout initRotation, you pick up the leg off the toolbox and it is oriented \u0022wrong\u0022 (easily fixed with a single tap of E) but attaches to the mating node correctly:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom toolbox:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022qnKDyxF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/qnKDyxF.png\u0022 width=\u0022879\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttached to node:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EcNEFfg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/EcNEFfg.png\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I add initRotation, the leg is oriented correctly when picked up from the toolbox, but then mates to the target node at the wrong angle:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom toolbox:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228NO1d7O.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022663\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/8NO1d7O.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttached to node:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00220q55goz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/0q55goz.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any documentation around for\u00A0initRotation? \u00A0Is it weird that it affects the direction at which your nodes mate?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(ps. Yes, I know that target node is floating out in the middle of nowhere :-) )\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-23T02:44:02Z\u0022 title=\u002210/23/2016 02:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 23, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-03T22:20:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing? \u00A0Anything?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}